watsup
February 14, 2019
Rating agencies are likely to downgrade South Africa if the government takes on more of Eskom’s debt.
Finance Minister Tito Mboweni is expected to detail government’s support for the power utility in his budget speech next week.
Economists say difficult political and policy decisions will have to be taken to stop the country’s public finances from deteriorating.
John Bailey has the story. Courtesy #DStv403
